@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“calem, post:3, topic:549088”][quote author=RandQm link=topic=667996.msg4467355#msg4467355 date=1420929573]
The easiest way is putting your project in an IDE like Eclipse or Netbeans which offers you the possibility to export the project as a runnable jar
[/quote]
iv tryed trust me its kinda hard i used eclipse .-. and ty for fast responce[/quote]
No, it’s really not.
You export it to a Runnable jar. Click the run settings you use for the client project. Click finish…

You can then use a tool like JARMaker (or even command line it) to sign the jar with whatever settings.

If you’re getting an error. Post it. Don’t post “I can’t do this” because that tells us nothing except that you have low expectations of yourself.
